problem link : https://leetcode.com/problems/insert-interval/description/

Intuition
So in this problem we need to insert a new interval into given intervals and merge if there are any overlapping intervals , the given inetrvals are already sorted from their starting point so the only interval that may be out of position is new interval , but instead of physically inserting it into the array, I carry it through the traversal. Whenever the current interval starts before it, I swap them so that my current candidate interval is always the one with the smaller start.

if theintervals overlap merge them by extendinf the ending point , otherwise the current interval is finalized and added to the answer , and we continue with next interval

Complexity
O(n)

Space complexity:
O(n)
Code
class Solution:
    def insert(self, iv: List[List[int]], newIv: List[int]) -> List[List[int]]:
        s1 = newIv[0]
        e1 = newIv[1]
        result = []
        for i in range(len(iv)):
            s2 = iv[i][0]
            e2 = iv[i][1]
            if s2 < s1:
                s1 , s2 = s2 , s1
                e1 , e2 = e2 , e1
            if e1 >= s2:
                e1 = max(e1,e2)
            else:
                result.append([s1,e1])
                s1 = s2
                e1 = e2
        result.append([s1,e1])
        return result
            
